XMRig is a high performance Monero (XMR) CPU miner, with official support for
Windows. Originally based on cpuminer-multi with heavy optimizations/rewrites
and removing a lot of legacy code, since version 1.0.0 completely rewritten from
scratch on C++.

Features

* High performance.
* Official Windows support.
* Small Windows executable, without dependencies.
* x86/x64 support.
* Support for backup (failover) mining server.
* keepalived support.
* Command line options compatible with cpuminer.
* CryptoNight-Lite support for AEON.
* Smart automatic CPU configuration.
* Nicehash support
* It's open source software.

Other information

* No HTTP support, only stratum protocol support.
* No TLS support.
* Default donation 5% (5 minutes in 100 minutes) can be reduced to 1% via
command line option --donate-level.
